Let the amount of caster sugar needed $= a$

Using equivalent ratio,

$
\begin{aligned}
8 \ \text{toffee apples} : 400 \ \text{g}       &= 24 \ \text{toffee apples} : a \ \text{g} \\\\
\dfrac{8} {400}                                 &= \dfrac {24} {a} \\\\
8 \times a                                      &= 24 \times 400 \\\\
a                                               &= \dfrac {24 \times 400} {8} \\\\
a                                               &= \dfrac {3 \times 8 \times 400} {8} \\\\
a                                               &= \dfrac {3 \times \cancel {8} \times 400} {\cancel {8}} \\\\
a                                               &= 3 \times 400 \\\\
a                                               &= 1200 \ \text{g}
\end{aligned}
$


$
\begin{aligned}
\text {Extra caster sugar to buy}   &= 1200 - 400 \\\\
                                    &= 800 \ \text{g}
\end{aligned}
$

